{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~kobsa/courses/ICS104/course-notes/what-are-ifs.htm", "content": "<!doctype html public \"-//w3c//dtd html 4.0 transitional//en\">\r<html>\r<head>\r   <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=iso-8859-1\">\r   <meta name=\"GENERATOR\" content=\"Mozilla/4.71 (Macintosh; I; PPC) [Netscape]\">\r   <title>What are interfaces?</title>\r</head>\r<body BGCOLOR=\"#FFFFFF\">\r<i><font size=\"+4\" face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">What are user interfaces?</font></i> \r<font face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><br> &nbsp;</font> <p>&nbsp;<p><FONT SIZE=\"5\" FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"> \r&nbsp;&nbsp;1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;User interfaces help users interact with \rprograms.</FONT> <FONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\" SIZE=\"5\"><br> &nbsp;&nbsp;2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Users \remploy programs for performing their tasks.</u> </FONT><br> \r<font face=\"Monotype Sorts\"><FONT SIZE=\"5\" FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><img src=\"../../../graphics/pointing-finger-right3.jpg\" width=\"62\" height=\"40\">&nbsp;</FONT></font><FONT SIZE=\"5\" FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\">User\rinterfaces \rhelp users <i>interact with their tasks.</i></FONT> \r<p>&nbsp;<TABLE WIDTH=\"761\" BORDER=\"0\" HEIGHT=\"88\"><TR><TD WIDTH=\"58\"><FONT FACE=\"Monotype Sorts\"><img src=\"../../../graphics/pointing-finger-right.jpg\" width=\"97\" height=\"69\"></FONT></TD>\r<TD WIDTH=\"693\"><FONT SIZE=\"5\" FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><I>A \ruser interface should not reflect the structure of the underlying program, but \rthe structure of the task domain and/or the task solution process. Users should \rnot interact with the computer, but with their tasks.</I></FONT> </TD></TR></TABLE><p>&nbsp;<p>&nbsp;<p><font face=\"Monotype Sorts\"></font>\r</body>\r</html>\r", "encoding": "ascii"}